From Mike Sixsmith Subject Re Please tell me they're not permenant scratches Catherine Barbara Saum writes Is there a way to wax out a dull finish minor scrathes While passngering on my fiance's Bandit my hip pack rubbed against the tail and left a nasty dull finish and teeny Is there a way to get rid of these Buff them out Wax them out help Car accessory shops here sell stuff called T Cut which is a very fine cutting paste for paint and this will remove the dull finish and minor It will also remove all the traffic film and stuff that you probably don't realise is there and give your paintwork its original lustre and It can sometimes react badly with metallic paint though so try it out carefully before going to town with the Afterwards apply wax polish and all will be well BTW don't confuse T cut with the cutting paste used for grinding in principle's the same but the coarseness is vastly Mike